WEBVTT

00:37.831 --> 00:41.727
BOY:
I remember that it hurt.

00:41.752 --> 00:45.214
Looking at her hurt.

01:01.647 --> 01:05.500
Your... your...
your nose.

01:05.525 --> 01:09.947
(WHISPERS)
Oh, oh, it does that sometimes.

01:12.366 --> 01:14.576
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

01:24.211 --> 01:26.380
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:34.721 --> 01:36.323
I never enjoy anything.

01:36.348 --> 01:39.201
I'm always waiting
for whatever's next.

01:39.226 --> 01:40.644
I think everyone's like that...

01:40.727 --> 01:42.246
living life in fast forward,

01:42.271 --> 01:43.914
never stopping to
enjoy the moment,

01:43.939 --> 01:46.333
too busy trying to rush
through everything,

01:46.358 --> 01:49.836
so we can get on with what we're really
supposed to be doing with our lives.

01:49.861 --> 01:53.048
I get these flashes of
clarity, brilliant clarity,

01:53.073 --> 01:55.217
where, for a second,
I stop and I think,

01:55.242 --> 01:57.386
"Wait, this is it."

01:57.411 --> 02:00.097
"This is my life. I'd better
slow down and enjoy it,"

02:00.122 --> 02:03.058
"because one day, we're all
going to end up in the ground,"

02:03.083 --> 02:05.335
"and that will be it.
We'll be gone."

02:06.920 --> 02:09.898
So I think we should fuck.
(CHOKES)

02:09.923 --> 02:12.150
Um... what?

02:12.175 --> 02:14.820
Let's just fast forward through all
the drunken seduction bullshit...

02:14.845 --> 02:16.738
we have to look forward to.

02:16.763 --> 02:19.283
You don't look like you'd
be very good at it anyway,

02:19.308 --> 02:21.994
and I don't want to sit here and listen
to you bumblefuck your way through it.

02:22.019 --> 02:24.204
We both want the same thing,

02:24.229 --> 02:26.957
to go back to your room, have sex,
and never see each other again.

02:26.982 --> 02:28.208
Are you with me?

02:28.233 --> 02:29.668
Is this a trick?

02:29.693 --> 02:31.169
The offer is about to expire.

02:31.194 --> 02:32.629
No, no, I'm in.

02:32.654 --> 02:33.864
I'm definitely in.

02:40.162 --> 02:41.179
Do you like that book?

02:41.204 --> 02:42.889
No, God, no.

02:42.914 --> 02:45.959
No, it's my idiot
brother's favorite book.

02:46.084 --> 02:47.936
- Is it yours?
- No, no.

02:47.961 --> 02:49.379
It's my roommate's.

02:51.131 --> 02:52.941
I'm not really much of a reader.

02:52.966 --> 02:55.177
Good.

02:58.221 --> 03:00.015
- Now come here.
- Yes, ma'am.

03:35.217 --> 03:39.780
(MAN AND WOMAN TALKING INSIDE)

03:39.805 --> 03:42.641
(COUPLE ARGUING)

04:02.202 --> 04:04.554
As I stood there staring
through the window

04:04.579 --> 04:06.515
into my ex-wife's
new life,

04:06.540 --> 04:09.393
I was overcome by the
oddest sensation.

04:09.418 --> 04:12.896
Watching her with this man was
like turning on a familiar sitcom

04:12.921 --> 04:17.149
and realizing they had replaced one
of the lead actors with a stranger.

04:17.175 --> 04:20.278
The show was the same, but the
thespian who played William Borgens

04:20.303 --> 04:23.365
for nearly twenty years was gone.

04:23.390 --> 04:26.535
And in his place was a
younger, dumber model.

04:26.560 --> 04:30.580
(BARKS)
(GASPS)

04:30.605 --> 04:32.082
MAN:
What was that, boy?

04:32.107 --> 04:33.107
Oh, shit.

04:35.735 --> 04:39.005
(BARKING, MAN YELLING)

04:39.030 --> 04:42.284
Down! Heel! Fucking dog!

05:17.694 --> 05:19.237
Rusty...

05:31.666 --> 05:33.043
Oh yeah.

05:36.880 --> 05:38.173
There you go.

05:43.595 --> 05:45.013
You got that bowl?

05:55.690 --> 05:57.192
Hey.

06:17.337 --> 06:20.690
Just rock it on there.
Get him on there.

06:20.715 --> 06:22.108
Gentle, gentle.
There you go.

06:22.133 --> 06:23.944
- Got it?
- Don't push that hard.

06:23.969 --> 06:25.111
All right.

06:25.136 --> 06:27.305
There we go.
Yeah.

06:48.118 --> 06:51.930
(KNOCKING)

06:51.955 --> 06:53.807
(KNOCKING AGAIN)

06:53.832 --> 06:55.600
Dad, she's here.

06:55.625 --> 06:59.020
(KNOCKING)

06:59.045 --> 07:00.589
Ready?

07:01.715 --> 07:03.758
Hi, I'm back.

07:07.137 --> 07:09.514
Dad...
(KNOCKING)

07:14.227 --> 07:15.270
Smells good.

07:21.318 --> 07:23.545
Well, they said that you
have to go back there?

07:23.570 --> 07:28.008
They just said that I think you
might have to end up paying for it.

07:28.033 --> 07:30.802
No, but they're going to cancel
the whole thing? The appointment?

07:30.827 --> 07:33.054
Yeah, they're canceling it.
It's over, basically...

07:33.079 --> 07:35.874
My book is being published!
(CHOKES)

07:39.544 --> 07:41.504
Oh, my God.
Congratulations.

07:41.630 --> 07:43.481
Thank you. Thanks, Dad.
Oh, my God.

07:43.506 --> 07:45.317
We're so proud of you.

07:45.342 --> 07:46.776
- What house is it?
- Scribner.

07:46.801 --> 07:48.820
What?
That's King's publisher.

07:48.845 --> 07:50.764
Yeah, no,
they're great. Great.

07:50.889 --> 07:53.491
We got to have a toast. We have
to have a toast. Scribner?

07:53.516 --> 07:56.911
Yeah, that's exactly what I was
thinking when I submitted the book.

07:56.936 --> 07:59.205
This will really piss Rusty off.

07:59.230 --> 08:02.542
It's not because they publish books
by Hemingway or Kurt Vonnegut.

08:02.567 --> 08:04.377
David McCullough, Frank McCourt.

08:04.402 --> 08:07.589
F. Scott Fitzgerald,
Bob fucking Dylan.

08:07.614 --> 08:09.341
I didn't know you had
dibs on Scribner.

08:09.366 --> 08:10.967
I never said I had
dibs, Samantha.

08:10.992 --> 08:12.719
- I just was...
- You're just jealous.

08:12.744 --> 08:14.137
- Wow.
- I'm not jealous.

08:14.162 --> 08:16.181
What an accomplishment.

08:16.206 --> 08:18.516
Your sister is having her first
book published, all right?

08:18.541 --> 08:20.226
This is a 'cause
for celebration.

08:20.251 --> 08:21.936
This is what the
holidays are all about.

08:21.961 --> 08:23.480
Okay, cool.

08:23.505 --> 08:25.023
You might want to
congratulate her.

08:25.048 --> 08:27.150
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

08:27.175 --> 08:29.569
Geez, I didn't have my first
book published until...

08:29.594 --> 08:33.365
I don't know.
I was 25 or 26.

08:33.390 --> 08:34.991
I would have been happy
to call those guys.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.451
I know them all over there.

08:36.476 --> 08:38.119
I submitted it under a fake name

08:38.144 --> 08:39.913
and didn't tell them
whose daughter I was

08:39.938 --> 08:41.998
until after was accepted.
I wouldn't have minded.

08:42.023 --> 08:43.875
I know. I just... Because you
wanted it to be about your book

08:43.900 --> 08:45.585
and not about being my daughter.

08:45.610 --> 08:48.947
Yeah. Okay, well, this
is a toast... psst.

08:50.824 --> 08:52.592
To you and your first novel.

08:52.617 --> 08:54.594
Just Saying Hi.

08:54.619 --> 08:57.889
Oh, it's not Just Saying Hi.

08:57.914 --> 08:59.766
Did they make you
change the title?

08:59.791 --> 09:02.227
No, they're not publishing
Just Saying Hi.

09:02.252 --> 09:04.212
It's a different book.

09:05.088 --> 09:06.381
What?

09:07.632 --> 09:09.776
I put that aside for now,

09:09.801 --> 09:11.319
and I wrote a new one.

09:11.344 --> 09:12.654
When?

09:12.679 --> 09:14.280
Over the summer.

09:14.305 --> 09:15.657
What happened to Just Saying Hi?

09:15.682 --> 09:17.617
You were excited about that.

09:17.642 --> 09:19.577
I was excit... I put a lot of
work and effort into that.

09:19.602 --> 09:21.121
I proofed the manuscript and I...

09:21.146 --> 09:22.872
I know.
I'm sorry. I...

09:22.897 --> 09:25.166
I..I..I thought my opinion
meant something.

09:25.191 --> 09:27.544
It does. Dad.
You know it does.

09:27.569 --> 09:30.213
And yet you turn around and
write an entirely new book

09:30.238 --> 09:32.157
and don't think to share it with me?

09:34.117 --> 09:35.577
I'm sorry.
(SIGHS)

09:38.705 --> 09:40.623
Something's burning.

09:46.254 --> 09:48.606
Congratulations.

09:48.631 --> 09:51.568
Why would you let him set
that place at the table?

09:51.593 --> 09:53.361
I set it.
He asked me to.

09:53.386 --> 09:55.155
Yeah, well, she's not coming.

09:55.180 --> 09:57.157
I'm about to head over there.
You should come.

09:57.182 --> 09:58.450
Give Dad a chance to cool off.

09:58.475 --> 09:59.868
I'm not going over there.

09:59.893 --> 10:01.202
Fine.
Suit yourself.

10:01.227 --> 10:02.620
I'll tell her you said hi.

10:02.645 --> 10:04.122
You can tell Mom to drop dead.

10:04.147 --> 10:06.608
(INHALES)
Whoa...

10:10.945 --> 10:14.407
(CAR RADIO)

10:29.130 --> 10:31.274
This food is so good.

10:31.299 --> 10:35.361
MOTHER:
Glad you like it.

10:35.386 --> 10:37.489
So how did everything
go over at your Dad's?

10:37.514 --> 10:41.367
It was good. Sam's getting
a book published.

10:41.392 --> 10:43.453
What?

10:43.478 --> 10:45.371
That was my reaction, too.

10:45.396 --> 10:47.791
That's great.

10:47.816 --> 10:50.835
I always thought your dad making you
and your sister keep journals was...

10:50.860 --> 10:53.797
a little strange, but...

10:53.822 --> 10:55.490
sounds like it's paying off.

10:55.615 --> 10:57.300
I can't believe it.

10:57.325 --> 10:58.635
Rusty, just let that go.

10:58.660 --> 11:00.512
No, why is it strange?

11:00.537 --> 11:02.555
I just want to know why you
think it's so strange.

11:02.580 --> 11:04.974
Well, it just seems
like he was forcing you

11:04.999 --> 11:06.643
to be writers...

11:06.668 --> 11:08.686
instead of allowing
you to choose to be.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.563
We don't have to keep the
journals if we don't want to.

11:10.588 --> 11:12.482
You'd have to get a
job if you stopped.

11:12.507 --> 11:14.609
He pays us to do it so we
can focus on our writing

11:14.634 --> 11:16.820
instead of working some
bullshit job at McDonald's.

11:16.845 --> 11:19.239
Rusty...

11:19.264 --> 11:21.366
What?

11:21.391 --> 11:22.742
What?

11:22.767 --> 11:24.244
Are you stoned?

11:24.269 --> 11:26.271
Are you kidding?
Are you being...

11:26.396 --> 11:29.249
I'm not stoned. Rusty, I'd like
to talk to you in the kitchen.

11:29.274 --> 11:31.000
I think you're stoned.

11:31.025 --> 11:33.069
- Great. Good.
- I'm going.

11:36.281 --> 11:37.715
(SIGHS)

11:37.740 --> 11:39.759
What's gotten into you?

11:39.784 --> 11:41.511
I'm not going to let
that Neanderthal...

11:41.536 --> 11:43.638
talk about Dad like that.

11:43.663 --> 11:45.431
He didn't say anything
about your father.

11:45.456 --> 11:47.725
It's not what he says.

11:47.750 --> 11:50.436
It's how he talks about him like he's
some sort of weirdo or something.

11:50.461 --> 11:52.313
And watching football doesn't
make you a Neanderthal.

11:52.338 --> 11:53.523
Owning his own gym does.

11:53.548 --> 11:55.258
Okay, enough.
Enough.

11:58.720 --> 12:02.448
Is Sam's book really getting published?

12:02.473 --> 12:04.158
That's what she said.

12:04.183 --> 12:06.352
(LAUGHS)
Wow.

12:11.232 --> 12:13.585
It's been over a
year since we spoke.

12:13.610 --> 12:14.903
I know.

12:16.362 --> 12:19.048
She said to say hi to you.

12:19.073 --> 12:23.469
I don't believe that
for a second, but...

12:23.494 --> 12:26.097
it's very sweet of you to say.

12:26.122 --> 12:28.516
Aw, Mom.
(SOBS)

12:28.541 --> 12:31.603
Please don't ever hate
me the way she hates me.

12:31.628 --> 12:33.354
I don't hate you at all, Mom.

12:33.379 --> 12:38.484
Good, but you are stoned,
though, aren't you.

12:38.509 --> 12:41.571
I thought it would make
it easier to eat again.

12:41.596 --> 12:44.282
Pot and nothing else,
ever, you understand me?

12:44.307 --> 12:45.700
You don't have to
worry about me, Mom.

12:45.725 --> 12:47.243
(WHISPERS)
Yeah, I do.

12:47.268 --> 12:48.853
It's my job.

12:57.153 --> 12:59.280
I cleared the table and
started the dishes.

13:01.074 --> 13:02.592
Sorry I reacted the way I did.

13:02.617 --> 13:04.260
I was just surprised.

13:04.285 --> 13:05.805
I thought you were
happy with the book.

13:05.828 --> 13:07.555
I was.

13:07.580 --> 13:10.975
It just didn't seem
like my book anymore.

13:11.000 --> 13:14.253
It felt like someone else's.

13:14.379 --> 13:17.548
My editorial hand a little
heavy for you? Yes, Dad.

13:21.052 --> 13:24.155
I was scared of how you'd react,

13:24.180 --> 13:28.159
and I felt guilty because of all the
work you put into Just Saying Hi.

13:28.184 --> 13:30.812
- I'm sorry...
- Stop apologizing.

13:33.648 --> 13:37.610
It's my fault for involving myself in
your goddamn book in the first place.

13:39.612 --> 13:42.365
(SIGHS) I'm guessing you don't
want to read the new one?

13:44.200 --> 13:46.386
Fuck no.

13:46.411 --> 13:49.555
- Never?
- No, thank you.

13:49.580 --> 13:51.057
I brought you a hard copy.

13:51.082 --> 13:52.850
- Really?
- Yeah.

13:52.875 --> 13:55.561
I was going to sign it
for you if you wanted,

13:55.586 --> 13:59.107
or not...
but maybe?

13:59.132 --> 14:00.550
Leave it on my desk.

14:04.804 --> 14:08.725
Wait... can I ask you a question
without you getting defensive?

14:12.270 --> 14:14.455
What?

14:14.480 --> 14:17.080
Rusty told me Martin called the
cops on a prowler the other night.

14:19.485 --> 14:22.196
Dad, you've got to stop doing this
to yourself. It's been two years.

14:22.321 --> 14:24.465
- She's coming back.
- You're completely delusional.

14:24.490 --> 14:26.367
And what's with setting a
place for her at the table?

14:26.492 --> 14:28.845
- That's fucking nuts.
- You know they're fighting again?

14:28.870 --> 14:30.054
And where did you see that?

14:30.079 --> 14:32.056
Through their window?

14:32.081 --> 14:34.392
Really? People get arrested
for doing things like that.

14:34.417 --> 14:36.102
You're a well respected novelist.

14:36.127 --> 14:38.187
You've won the PEN
Faulkner Award twice.

14:38.212 --> 14:39.731
You can't behave like that.

14:39.756 --> 14:41.524
She's coming back.

14:41.549 --> 14:43.718
Jesus, at least tell me
you've been writing.

14:46.220 --> 14:47.972
Look at what you've let
her do to you, Dad.

14:50.433 --> 14:52.560
Seriously.

15:04.489 --> 15:07.200
(KNOCKING)

15:07.325 --> 15:11.179
- Hey.
- What are you working on?

15:11.204 --> 15:14.265
It's a poem for English class.

15:14.290 --> 15:17.310
Sorry about earlier.
I was being a dick.

15:17.335 --> 15:18.936
It's okay.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.563
Yeah, you were right.
I was just jealous.

15:20.588 --> 15:22.690
I really am happy for you.
It's awesome.

15:22.715 --> 15:25.193
You're going to have a book
published one day, too, you know.

15:25.218 --> 15:26.260
Sure, I know.

15:28.137 --> 15:30.139
Jason hooked me up
with some weed.

15:32.934 --> 15:34.143
Roof?

15:36.104 --> 15:38.439
Got your eye on any
girls this year?

15:41.275 --> 15:43.236
Yeah, there's this girl...

15:45.113 --> 15:47.924
Kate, in my English class.

15:47.949 --> 15:50.243
Every time I see her,
I hear that song,

15:50.368 --> 15:53.471
the Beatles' song, "ve Just Seen a
Face," playing in my head. (COUGHS)

15:53.496 --> 15:55.348
God, you are so pathetic.

15:55.373 --> 15:57.100
At least I know I'm pathetic.

15:57.125 --> 15:58.851
Let me give you some advice.

15:58.876 --> 16:00.156
I can't wait to
hear your advice.

16:00.169 --> 16:02.605
It's so friggin' awesome.

16:02.630 --> 16:05.091
There are two kinds of
people in this world.

16:05.216 --> 16:09.362
Hopeless romantics and realists.
Right.

16:09.387 --> 16:11.864
A realist just sees that face

16:11.889 --> 16:15.118
and packs it in with every other
pretty girl they've ever seen before.

16:15.143 --> 16:18.496
The hopeless romantic
becomes convinced

16:18.521 --> 16:22.291
that God put them on Earth
to be with that one person.

16:22.316 --> 16:24.752
But there is no God,

16:24.777 --> 16:29.132
and life is only as meaningful as you
fool yourself into thinking it is.

16:29.157 --> 16:31.884
Guys who get laid a
lot are realists.

16:31.909 --> 16:33.703
You should be listening.

16:35.580 --> 16:38.182
Just avoid love at all costs.

16:38.207 --> 16:39.500
That's my motto.

16:43.546 --> 16:45.982
Never been in love?

16:46.007 --> 16:49.235
If love is setting a place at the table
for someone who is never coming home,

16:49.260 --> 16:50.761
I think I'll pass.

16:52.263 --> 16:54.490
That's fucking depressing, Sam.

16:54.515 --> 16:57.660
Making students read their poetry
assignments in front of the class

16:57.685 --> 16:59.871
is a sadistic exercise
in public humiliation.

16:59.896 --> 17:01.831
You could have already been
done with it by now, Rusty.

17:01.856 --> 17:03.499
- Okay, okay, okay.
- Just read it.

17:03.524 --> 17:05.542
(GROANS)

17:05.568 --> 17:10.131
Um, okay, this is a poem I
wrote over Thanksgiving break.

17:10.156 --> 17:13.800
Uh...
It's called School.

17:13.826 --> 17:16.345
It was written under the
influence of cannabis.

17:16.369 --> 17:18.681
(STUDENTS LAUGH)

17:18.705 --> 17:22.685
Okay, um... In the sea
of... This is so awkward.

17:22.710 --> 17:24.686
Uh...
(GROANS)

17:24.712 --> 17:27.522
"In the sea of desks, there's
talk of games and bags"

17:27.548 --> 17:32.403
"and long pipes that leak dreams
with the strike of a match."

17:32.428 --> 17:34.614
"And there's a loudness
to the whispers I hear."

17:34.639 --> 17:37.909
"Whispers shouldn't be
that loud, should they?"

17:37.934 --> 17:40.036
"There's a girl over
there who everyone knows"

17:40.061 --> 17:44.248
"and men without ears who will
stand by the door for a price."

17:44.273 --> 17:47.627
"In long hallways, there are
angry mobs of dwarves and rats"

17:47.652 --> 17:49.278
"and one single angel."

17:57.703 --> 17:59.597
Hey, Rusty. Hi.

17:59.622 --> 18:04.227
Hi. Hi, I, um... I
liked your poem.

18:04.252 --> 18:07.897
- Yeah?
- Yeah, it was really good.

18:07.922 --> 18:11.442
- Thanks.
- Sure.

18:11.467 --> 18:13.861
How was your Thanksgiving?

18:13.886 --> 18:16.572
Oh, it was good.
It was a little weird.

18:16.597 --> 18:19.909
My parents are divorced,
so I have two Thanksgivings

18:19.934 --> 18:21.519
in one Thanksgiving.

18:21.644 --> 18:23.412
It's just, like, strange.
(GIGGLES)

18:23.437 --> 18:25.064
How about you?

18:25.189 --> 18:27.375
- It was just boring. Whatever.
- That's cool.

18:27.400 --> 18:29.543
(WHISPERS)
Yeah.

18:29.568 --> 18:32.588
Kate.

18:32.613 --> 18:34.548
I have to go.

18:34.573 --> 18:38.886
I just wanted to say I
liked your poem, so...

18:38.911 --> 18:40.955
Bye.
All right.

18:43.499 --> 18:44.892
Who the fuck is that?

18:44.917 --> 18:46.460
Just a guy from class.

18:49.005 --> 18:50.923
Fucking asshole.

19:02.393 --> 19:04.453
Hi.

19:04.478 --> 19:07.999
I literally have 20 minutes,
so it will have to be quick.

19:08.024 --> 19:09.458
Come on.
Let's go.

19:09.483 --> 19:10.483
Did you stretch?

19:15.323 --> 19:16.824
Come on.

19:19.910 --> 19:21.262
Just a second.

19:21.287 --> 19:23.097
Oh, yeah.

19:23.122 --> 19:24.974
Oh, make it rain.

19:24.999 --> 19:27.168
Yeah.
(GASPS)

19:29.795 --> 19:32.231
Yeah.
To the left.

19:32.256 --> 19:34.091
To the...
yeah.

