37:25.161 --> 37:26.913
Just think about it.

37:38.842 --> 37:41.903
Procreation. You give to the
next one down the line.

37:41.928 --> 37:43.488
That's really all we've got.

37:43.513 --> 37:45.865
Society, government, money, religion,

37:45.890 --> 37:48.451
careers, nuclear families, monogamy.

37:48.476 --> 37:51.788
These are all just highly creative
socially accepted delusions

37:51.813 --> 37:56.292
that we impose on reality to try and gain
some semblance of control over our lives.

37:56.317 --> 37:58.294
It gives us the illusion of choice.

37:58.319 --> 38:02.006
It makes us feel a little
less like animals.

38:02.031 --> 38:04.467
Animals. What do you mean?
Like evolution?

38:04.492 --> 38:06.469
Yeah, evolution, exactly.

38:06.494 --> 38:08.304
I do not believe in evolution.

38:08.329 --> 38:11.141
There's 400 billion stars
in the Milky Way alone,

38:11.166 --> 38:13.143
making the amount of stars
in the entire universe

38:13.168 --> 38:15.562
completely mindboggling.

38:15.587 --> 38:17.439
We are nothing.

38:17.464 --> 38:19.566
If an asteroid hadn't hit
Earth 65 million years ago

38:19.591 --> 38:20.942
and wiped out all the dinosaurs,

38:20.967 --> 38:22.944
we wouldn't be here.

38:22.969 --> 38:25.613
Yeah.
I'm going to go.

38:25.638 --> 38:31.161
Good. All you creationists do is
blow chances at getting laid.

38:31.186 --> 38:34.873
- Really.
- Ooh, that was awkward.

38:34.898 --> 38:37.041
You've really got to stop stalking me.

38:37.066 --> 38:39.903
I can't even go anywhere without
you showing up to annoy me.

38:40.028 --> 38:42.589
- Were you hitting on that guy?
- It's none of your business.

38:42.614 --> 38:44.132
I think he's a Mormon.

38:44.157 --> 38:45.800
Well, what the hell
is he doing here?

38:45.825 --> 38:47.886
Trying to find other
Mormon girls.

38:47.911 --> 38:51.681
I'm sure you corrupted him,
ruined his relationship with God.

38:51.706 --> 38:53.183
You want to get out of here?

38:53.208 --> 38:55.435
Do you have brain damage?

38:55.460 --> 38:57.479
No. I think I made
it pretty clear

38:57.504 --> 38:59.647
that I have absolutely no
interest in going out with you.

38:59.672 --> 39:01.900
No, no, no. You and I
are going to be friends.

39:01.925 --> 39:03.735
But I don't want to be friends with you.

39:03.760 --> 39:06.237
(WHISPERS)
Oh, you don't want to be.

39:06.262 --> 39:08.364
Well, I'm going to
take your jacket

39:08.389 --> 39:10.575
and you can follow me. We can
get some coffee if you'd like.

39:10.600 --> 39:13.828
I need that...

39:13.853 --> 39:15.371
jacket.

39:15.396 --> 39:19.334
What are some of
your favorite books?

39:19.359 --> 39:21.920
Is that really the angle
you're going to play?

39:21.945 --> 39:25.573
Really? I thought you'd be
more creative than this.

39:25.698 --> 39:29.469
Well, come on, we're writers, right?
Yeah.

39:29.494 --> 39:32.263
Books matter to us. I mean,
come on here, please.

39:32.288 --> 39:35.767
Fine, what are some of
your favorite books?

39:35.792 --> 39:37.727
No, you can't do that.
I asked you.

39:37.752 --> 39:39.832
Because you want to know
something personal about me.

39:39.837 --> 39:42.106
If I tell you what my
favorite books are,

39:42.131 --> 39:44.400
you'll say titles that will
convince me that we're soulmates,

39:44.425 --> 39:46.402
or you'll latch onto
one of my favorites

39:46.427 --> 39:48.321
and try to convince me it's
one of your favorites, too.

39:48.346 --> 39:49.781
God, you're so tough.

39:49.806 --> 39:51.157
It's why you're
obsessed with me.

39:51.182 --> 39:52.492
I'm not obsessed with you.

39:52.517 --> 39:54.118
I'm like a unicorn to you.

39:54.143 --> 39:55.954
You'll do or say
anything to possess me.

39:55.979 --> 39:58.248
I'm not like that and
you're not like a unicorn.

39:58.273 --> 40:00.208
Okay, well, then books.

40:00.233 --> 40:02.418
But please, at least
attempt to be interesting.

40:02.443 --> 40:04.921
No Catcher in the Rye or
Portnoy's Complaint, okay?

40:04.946 --> 40:09.259
Well, I write mysteries, so...

40:09.284 --> 40:12.262
I love Elmore Leonard,
James Lee Burke,

40:12.287 --> 40:13.930
Ed Brubaker.

40:13.955 --> 40:16.391
Who's Ed Brubaker.

40:16.416 --> 40:20.270
He writes an incredible, hard-boiled
crime comic called Criminal.

40:20.295 --> 40:22.564
Telling me that you
read comic books

40:22.589 --> 40:25.233
isn't exactly sweeping
me off my feet.

40:25.258 --> 40:27.277
What's your favorite book?

40:27.302 --> 40:29.302
Just say the first thing
that pops into your head.

40:30.388 --> 40:32.432
Dear Mr. Henshaw
by Beverly Cleary.

40:34.142 --> 40:36.369
Been my favorite
since I was a kid.

40:36.394 --> 40:38.204
Read it, like, 100 times.

40:38.229 --> 40:41.107
It's actually what made
me want to be a writer.

40:42.442 --> 40:43.442
Hey, is something wrong?

40:43.443 --> 40:45.420
I have to go.

40:45.445 --> 40:47.255
Well, what... what do you mean?
Did I do something?

40:47.280 --> 40:48.756
I have to go.

40:48.781 --> 40:49.824
Samantha.

40:52.243 --> 40:54.470
- Samantha, wait. Come on.
- What?

40:54.495 --> 40:56.180
What do you want from me?

40:56.205 --> 40:57.724
What do you mean what
do I want from you?

40:57.749 --> 40:59.208
I like you.

40:59.334 --> 41:00.960
- I want to get to know you better.
- No.

41:01.085 --> 41:02.979
- Why do you keep running away?
- Because this...

41:03.004 --> 41:05.023
whatever this is between us,
it can't go any further.

41:05.048 --> 41:07.817
I won't let it. We're not
even in the same species.

41:07.842 --> 41:10.612
Is Dear Mr. Henshaw
your favorite book, too?

41:10.637 --> 41:12.280
I don't do this, Lou.

41:12.305 --> 41:13.781
No.
No, of course not.

41:13.806 --> 41:15.617
You just give yourself away

41:15.642 --> 41:17.810
to assholes with infinitely
lower IQs than yours.

41:23.983 --> 41:25.460
Fuck.

41:25.485 --> 41:28.755
(KNOCKING)

41:28.780 --> 41:31.115
Hi.
Hi.

41:32.575 --> 41:34.510
Is your dad here?

41:34.535 --> 41:36.012
Uh, no...

41:36.037 --> 41:38.640
Well, when is he going to be back?

41:38.665 --> 41:42.185
I don't know. Maybe
a couple of hours.

41:42.210 --> 41:43.853
Why?

41:43.878 --> 41:47.674
I want to give you your Christmas present.

41:51.094 --> 41:52.929
Um, okay.

42:03.606 --> 42:04.707
Merry Christmas.

42:04.732 --> 42:07.168
Oh...
awesome.

42:07.193 --> 42:09.420
Come with me.

42:09.445 --> 42:10.838
Where are we going?

42:10.863 --> 42:12.507
To the closet.

42:12.532 --> 42:15.093
Wait, why the closet?
Why not on the bed?

42:15.118 --> 42:17.387
Can we open it?
(LAUGHS)

42:17.412 --> 42:22.600
Because you've never had sex,

42:22.625 --> 42:27.563
and I've never had sex in a closet.

42:27.588 --> 42:32.110
You'll remember me and
you'll remember this moment

42:32.135 --> 42:35.054
and that makes me very, very happy.

42:45.148 --> 42:47.900
(RUSTY AND KATE LAUGHING)

43:23.436 --> 43:24.436
Oh, fuck.

43:31.736 --> 43:33.279
Hi.

43:36.115 --> 43:37.675
How's she feeling?

43:37.700 --> 43:40.203
She's okay. You
should go see her.

43:59.055 --> 44:00.348
How you feeling?

44:02.767 --> 44:04.535
Not too bad.

44:04.560 --> 44:06.120
Don't bullshit me.

44:06.145 --> 44:08.206
I'm like a no bullshit detector here.

44:08.231 --> 44:11.083
I'm fine.

44:11.108 --> 44:13.736
- Shut up and read to me.
- Okay.

44:24.622 --> 44:28.893
"Dalie Hallie couldn't tell
if she felt huge or small."

44:28.918 --> 44:31.395
"She wondered whether her head"

44:31.420 --> 44:34.941
"were so big as to be able to
contain all this starry universe..."

44:34.966 --> 44:37.610
"or if the universe were so
little that it would fit"

44:37.635 --> 44:40.238
"within the compass
of her human head."

44:40.263 --> 44:42.949
Lou?

44:42.974 --> 44:45.660
Do you see that
angel by the door

44:45.685 --> 44:47.854
or am I the only one seeing her?

44:54.068 --> 44:58.072
Oh, that... that's definitely
not an angel, Mom.

45:04.245 --> 45:06.706
Hi.
Hi.

45:06.831 --> 45:09.267
Hi. What are you doing here?

45:09.292 --> 45:11.978
Oh, same thing you're
doing, I hope.

45:12.003 --> 45:13.563
Don't be suspicious.

45:13.588 --> 45:16.399
I'm getting a laptop
for Samantha.

45:16.424 --> 45:19.360
In fact, I got to pick out a color.
Why don't you come?

45:19.385 --> 45:21.195
I don't know.
Excuse me.

45:21.220 --> 45:23.614
Huh?
What don't you know?

45:23.639 --> 45:26.659
I don't know if it's a good idea, Bill.

45:26.684 --> 45:29.537
It will take ten minutes.

45:29.562 --> 45:30.872
I'd love to.
Yeah.

45:30.897 --> 45:33.291
Yeah?
Yeah, I'd love to.

45:33.316 --> 45:35.918
I'm glad I bumped into you.

45:35.943 --> 45:38.421
I'm sure that's what all stalkers say.

45:38.446 --> 45:41.883
No, really.

45:41.908 --> 45:44.118
I've been thinking a lot
about what you said.

45:44.243 --> 45:46.304
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

45:46.329 --> 45:48.598
Somebody else said the
same thing recently.

45:48.623 --> 45:51.667
Someone else asked you to stop
hanging around their house at night?

45:53.377 --> 45:55.338
About moving on with my life.

45:57.381 --> 45:59.358
Who was that?

45:59.383 --> 46:01.152
Tricia Wolcott.

46:01.177 --> 46:02.987
Lives about a mile and
a half down the beach.

46:03.012 --> 46:04.864
Yeah, I remember her.
Yeah.

46:04.889 --> 46:07.909
Yeah.
Yeah.

46:07.934 --> 46:10.828
I always suspected you
had a crush on her.

46:10.853 --> 46:12.705
Yeah, she's very pretty.

46:12.730 --> 46:15.441
She's very married, as I recall.

46:17.693 --> 46:19.462
You're seeing her?

46:19.487 --> 46:21.297
I think I'm a good way
for her to kill an hour

46:21.322 --> 46:23.115
after she drops her
kids off at school.

46:24.533 --> 46:25.718
An hour?

46:25.743 --> 46:27.720
An hour.

46:27.745 --> 46:31.933
So she thinks you need to
stop moping around, too, huh?

46:31.958 --> 46:34.560
Something like that.

46:34.585 --> 46:36.253
Here's a confession.

46:38.005 --> 46:39.840
I'm not a great writer.

46:41.592 --> 46:44.153
I'm a great
re-writer.

46:44.178 --> 46:46.222
I think about us.

46:47.306 --> 46:48.991
Our story and...

46:49.016 --> 46:51.160
and all the things that
went wrong with us

46:51.185 --> 46:54.146
and I... I could do it so
much better this time.

46:58.401 --> 47:00.670
I haven't written
anything since you left.

47:00.695 --> 47:02.672
Bill...

47:02.697 --> 47:04.757
you've had two books published.

47:04.782 --> 47:07.760
Well, they were books that I
started when we were married.

47:07.785 --> 47:09.720
I finished them, but I haven't
written anything new.

47:09.745 --> 47:11.973
You are a great writer.

47:11.998 --> 47:15.167
Don't waste all your
imagination on me.

47:21.382 --> 47:22.483
Which way are you...

47:22.508 --> 47:24.485
I'm over here.

47:24.510 --> 47:26.570
I'm the other way.

47:26.595 --> 47:29.407
It was great running into you.

47:29.432 --> 47:32.076
You, too.

47:32.101 --> 47:33.811
Bill...

47:37.523 --> 47:42.962
I have... I have days when I'm not
sure if I made the right decision.

47:42.987 --> 47:45.197
I have bad days, too.

47:48.534 --> 47:50.928
I don't know why I'm saying this.

47:50.953 --> 47:54.015
I guess I just don't want you to
think that I don't think about us,

47:54.040 --> 47:56.684
you know, and...

47:56.709 --> 47:58.144
all those years we
spent together,

47:58.169 --> 47:59.228
because I do...

47:59.253 --> 48:01.605
think about...

48:01.630 --> 48:03.591
everything that I gave up.

48:06.302 --> 48:08.345
I wonder if it was worth it.

48:10.181 --> 48:11.724
Was it?

48:17.938 --> 48:20.291
I got to go.
(SIGHS)

48:20.316 --> 48:21.776
Merry Christmas.

48:24.737 --> 48:26.447
Merry Christmas.

48:29.283 --> 48:31.635
It was so nice to meet you.

48:31.660 --> 48:34.055
Oh, you, too, Samantha.

48:34.080 --> 48:36.557
I hope you come back
and see me again soon.

48:36.582 --> 48:38.225
- I will.
- Okay, you two.

48:38.250 --> 48:39.643
I'm going to walk
Sam to her car.

48:39.668 --> 48:41.729
I'll be right back, Mom.

48:41.754 --> 48:43.898
CARETAKER: Not so fast.
I made hot chocolate.

48:43.923 --> 48:45.049
It's in the kitchen.

48:46.801 --> 48:49.512
What's wrong with your mom?

48:51.722 --> 48:55.785
She, um...
She has a brain tumor.

48:55.810 --> 48:58.604
Oh, my God.
I'm sorry.

49:02.608 --> 49:05.002
I can't believe how much of
a bitch I've been to you.

49:05.027 --> 49:07.004
Yeah, I know, right?

49:07.029 --> 49:09.715
Okay, yeah.

49:09.740 --> 49:14.637
I don't... I don't want you
to feel sorry for me.

49:14.662 --> 49:18.140
Really, I...

49:18.165 --> 49:21.435
I've enjoyed all of our back
and forth, you know, sparring.

49:21.460 --> 49:24.355
It's really... it's helped me
take my mind off of all this.

49:24.380 --> 49:28.134
Well, I'm glad I could help out.

49:29.802 --> 49:31.570
You going home for Christmas?

49:31.595 --> 49:33.973
Yeah, I'm headed back there tomorrow.

49:36.142 --> 49:41.580
Well, I'm willing to forget about
this whole stalking incident,

49:41.605 --> 49:44.125
if you will allow me to take you out

49:44.150 --> 49:46.085
on a proper date when you get back.

49:46.110 --> 49:47.319
Okay.

49:49.071 --> 49:50.464
Really?
That easy? Yeah?

49:50.489 --> 49:52.842
I'm not going to say it again.

49:52.867 --> 49:54.510
Okay.

49:54.535 --> 49:57.596
Oh, I actually...

49:57.621 --> 50:02.585
brought you an ARC of my new book.

50:02.710 --> 50:06.355
Oh, wow. Stalking and a present.

50:06.380 --> 50:11.694
Under the Pink by Samantha Borgens.
Look at that.

50:11.719 --> 50:18.409
Well, I will... I will
read this over break.

50:18.434 --> 50:20.452
Probably aloud.

50:20.477 --> 50:23.080
My mom and I have been tearing
through some books lately.

50:23.105 --> 50:25.291
No, you can't read it to her.

50:25.316 --> 50:27.710
It's filled with sex and profanity.

50:27.735 --> 50:29.862
Oh, no, she loves sex.

50:32.489 --> 50:34.675
SAMANTHA:
You added too much water.

50:34.700 --> 50:37.303
BILL: It's not like you're
Martha Stewart in here.

50:37.328 --> 50:41.665
Says the guy who puts sprinkles on burn.

50:41.790 --> 50:43.559
Hey, guys.

50:43.584 --> 50:44.894
Look at you!

50:44.919 --> 50:46.312
Why are you all dressed up?

50:46.337 --> 50:47.897
I'm going over to Kate's.

50:47.922 --> 50:49.565
Why does it smell so horrible in here?

50:49.590 --> 50:51.609
No, no, no. These are our cookies.
Smell.

50:51.634 --> 50:53.485
Yeah, we burned the first batch.

50:53.510 --> 50:55.362
Actually, this is the second.
(FIRE ALARM BEEPS)

50:55.387 --> 50:57.531
No, no, no, no, no!

50:57.556 --> 51:00.434
Sorry!

51:00.559 --> 51:02.578
Oh, my God, Dad!
What?

51:02.603 --> 51:04.121
This is ridiculous!

51:04.146 --> 51:05.748
We burned them again!

51:05.773 --> 51:06.999
Oh, God. Okay...
(LAUGHING)

51:07.024 --> 51:09.293
Yeah, no laughing, Rusty.

51:09.318 --> 51:11.420
When am I going to meet this girl?

51:11.445 --> 51:13.380
I don't know. Try not
to burn the house down.

51:13.405 --> 51:14.423
Yeah, drive careful.

51:14.448 --> 51:15.616
I will.

51:17.493 --> 51:19.553
How serious is this thing?

51:19.578 --> 51:21.722
Uh, they're having sex.

51:21.747 --> 51:24.833
What?
How do you know?

51:24.959 --> 51:28.479
Yeah.
Wow, go Rusty!

51:28.504 --> 51:30.189
She has more experience than him.

51:30.214 --> 51:32.191
Yeah, well, who doesn't?

51:32.216 --> 51:34.426
He seems really happy.

51:35.928 --> 51:37.655
At least someone in this house is.

51:37.680 --> 51:40.532
Do you see a frown on my face?

51:40.557 --> 51:43.577
You do seem unusually chipper today.

51:43.602 --> 51:45.412
Have you discovered
anti-depressants?

51:45.437 --> 51:49.708
Actually, no. I'm just
moving on with my life.

51:49.733 --> 51:51.418
I'm done with the whole
thing with your mom,

51:51.443 --> 51:53.379
and I'm moving forward.

51:53.404 --> 51:56.090
Seriously?

51:56.115 --> 51:58.008
New Year's resolution.

51:58.033 --> 51:59.927
How about that?
Moving on.

51:59.952 --> 52:01.595
Dad?
Yeah.

52:01.620 --> 52:02.930
That's huge!

52:02.955 --> 52:05.099
That's so...
Oh, flour hug.

52:05.124 --> 52:08.394
No, no, no!

52:08.419 --> 52:09.728
Not on my white shirt.

52:09.753 --> 52:11.605
Ta-da!

52:11.630 --> 52:13.630
I thought you already gave
me my Christmas present.

52:13.632 --> 52:15.776
Shut up and open it.
Come on.

52:15.801 --> 52:18.012
All right, here we go.

52:20.139 --> 52:21.615
This isn't just a CD.

52:21.640 --> 52:23.117
It isn't?
No.

52:23.142 --> 52:26.020
It's a roadmap to my soul.

52:27.688 --> 52:29.415
It's like if you gave me a favorite book.

52:29.440 --> 52:32.376
Yeah, speaking of that.

52:32.401 --> 52:33.711
Boom.

52:33.736 --> 52:35.404
Oh, my gosh.

52:39.241 --> 52:42.886
Wow, this is the biggest
book I've ever seen.

52:42.911 --> 52:44.430
I know it looks formidable,

52:44.455 --> 52:46.515
but honestly, it's going to be, like,

52:46.540 --> 52:49.101
one of the most satisfying reading
experiences of your life.

52:49.126 --> 52:50.853
Is it scary?

52:50.878 --> 52:52.813
Yeah, sure, but it's not just a scary book.

52:52.838 --> 52:54.565
It's like Moby Dick.
It's about everything.

52:54.590 --> 52:56.567
You're going to be so wrapped up in it,

52:56.592 --> 52:58.819
you're going to be crying at
the end of it. You cried.

52:58.844 --> 53:00.404
Oh, you'll cry, too, okay?

53:00.429 --> 53:01.847
I might have cried.

53:04.600 --> 53:07.895
You're really cute when you
get worked up about books.

53:12.441 --> 53:15.794
Do I have you worked up about me?

53:15.819 --> 53:18.130
Yeah.
Good.

53:18.155 --> 53:21.342
Because I've got to have you right now.

53:21.367 --> 53:23.218
What about your parents?
Won't they come in?

53:23.243 --> 53:25.621
They don't come in here.

53:25.746 --> 53:28.040
Are you sure? I'm sure.
Come here.

53:32.378 --> 53:33.854
LOU:
How was your Christmas?

53:33.879 --> 53:35.522
It was good.

53:35.547 --> 53:38.133
Filled with family. You know, loud.
Yeah.

53:41.053 --> 53:44.239
So you haven't mentioned my book.

53:44.264 --> 53:47.326
Mm. Yeah, um...

53:47.351 --> 53:48.577
So you didn't like it?

53:48.602 --> 53:50.079
No, no, that's not it.

53:50.104 --> 53:51.413
I liked it a lot.

53:51.438 --> 53:53.791
It's incredibly well written.

53:53.816 --> 53:57.711
The characters are vibrant and alive.

53:57.736 --> 53:59.213
But?

53:59.238 --> 54:01.256
I mean, I knew you were cynical,

54:01.281 --> 54:06.428
but is that really how you
feel about love and marriage?

54:06.453 --> 54:09.973
I don't know.
Sometimes.

54:09.998 --> 54:12.209
Oh, thank you.

54:16.463 --> 54:18.148
How much of that really happened?

54:18.173 --> 54:21.026
I made most of it up.

54:21.051 --> 54:23.070
I didn't draw that much
from my parents' divorce,

54:23.095 --> 54:24.947
